<Base title="About" description="About Robert Slowinski — amateur photographer based in Boulder, Colorado">

  <div class="about-wrap">

    <div class="about-photos">
      <img src="/images/about/self.jpg" alt="Robert Slowinski" />
    </div>

    <div class="about-bio">
      <h1>Robert Slowinski</h1>
      <p class="location">Boulder, Colorado</p>

      <p>
        Welcome. This space is a visual archive of over twenty years behind the lens, capturing details across Western Europe, the American West, South America, and further afield.
      </p>

      <p>
        I first got into photography during college, starting in the year 2000 with a (film!) Nikon N65 and a primitive Kodak DC280 digital camera. From there, my toolkit evolved alongside the technology—transitioning through compact Micro Four-Thirds and Fujifilm APS-C cameras and landing on various iterations of the Sony A7 series. Over the years, I've developed a preference for prime lenses; the constraint and having to "zoom with your feet" requires a more deliberate, physical approach to framing that forces a bit more consideration.
      </p>

      <div class="contact">
        Print &amp; licensing inquiries: <a href="mailto:rfslowphoto@gmail.com">rfslowphoto@gmail.com</a>
      </div>
    </div>

  </div>

</Base>
